version_description: This is how I play 'Here We Stand'. The chords in the Chorus and Bridge differs from the previous version.

This has the actual chords that the Newsboys play on the recording. There was not a version available that I could use to play along with the song.  This is in the key of D, which no other version has.

version_description: This is the correct Key and the correct chords in the verses and bridge. one other version uses a capo on the first fret and it would work except that all the verses and bridge use a B and it should be a G
Other versions either don't have sections labeled properly and none have pre-chorus part labeled. its not part of vrs1 or the chorus as in other versions. minor edit to get it right.
This is the first tab of this song, and I may make another one because the synthesizer and vocals have different chords. It sounds like Eb and Bb work but the synth plays Bb and then F.

The player will want to alter which strings are muted on these indicated chords throughout the song and/or add extra notes while strumming. The G3 and D5 chords indicate them being barred on the 3rd and 5th fret when the song calls for it after the guitar solo. The intro and guitar solo tabs are included as well. Enjoy this phenomenal song by Newsboys https://youtu.be/tFho9zJFR2U.
